data.title: Yorkwood Homes
data.text:
Godfrey & Cappe began building in Don Mills and ultimately built over 1,000 homes

Jonat Construction began building townhomes and apartment buildings

Victoria Wood was created. It became Canada's largest homebuilder, building more than 1,400 homes a year

Joe Godfrey becomes a member of the Toronto Home Builders' Board of Directors

Yorkwood Homes / Yorkwood Investments starts building new homes and communities

Yorkwood completes Charles Promenade Towers in the heart of Toronto

Norman Godfrey elected 1985 President of the Toronto Home Builders' Association

Joe Godfrey inducted into the Toronto Home Builders' Hall of Fame for his outstanding contribution to the industry

Norman Godfrey elected President of Canadian Home Builders' Association

Myer Godfrey elected Chairman of Greater Toronto Builder Industry Liaison Committee

Myer Godfrey elected 2nd Vice-President of the Greater Toronto Home Builders' Association

Myer Godfrey elected 1st Vice-President of the Greater Toronto Home Builders' Association

Myer Godfrey elected President of the Greater Toronto Home Builders' Association

Myer Godfrey receives Rooftopper of the Year Award from the Canadian Home Builders' Association

Norman Godfrey inducted into the Toronto Home Builders' Hall of Fame for his outstanding contribution to the industry

Yorkwood Homes receives Building Award of Excellence from the Town of Markham

Yorkwood Homes Brookside Community is awarded "Best Lowrise Community in the GTA"

Yorkwood Homes nominated for the Ernest Ashly Award for the Ontario Home Warranty Program

Markham Design Excellence Award

Markham Building Excellence Award for "large volume" - in recognition of excellent compliance to The Building Code Act, Building Code Knowledge, Site Administration

Markham Building Excellence Award for "large volume" - in recognition of excellent compliance to The Building Code Act, Building Code Knowledge, Site Administration
